Colshorrock wrote a review Oct 2019
Pattaya, Thailand41 contributions34 helpful votes
Noise
Booked direct and have an ocean view suite, the rooms are very nice and well appointed. No mention from the management when booking however that there is a hotel of some sort being built directly next door to the property so during the day the hammering etc can be heard in the room. Nice rooftop pool but no relaxing due to the excessive noise from the building work. Good hotel managers inform potential bookers of such problems during the booking process, but it seems the managment of A La carte feel it is better for guests to find this out after they have paid good money. If you come for peace and quiet to Da Nang, stay well away from this hotel.
Date of stay: October 2019
Responded Oct 14, 2019
Xin chào Colshorrock, First of all, we would like to thank you for choosing us for your stay in Da Nang. We are obviously disappointed that you did not like your stay at À La Carte Da Nang Beach due to near by construction which is out of our hotel control. Your feedback has been shared with relevant management team for review and action. Once again, we appreciate your sharing your concerns, and it is our hope that you will give us the opportunity to better serve you in the near future. Sincerely, The A La Carte management team.
